The paper discusses a new type of non-volatile memory that is secure against various types of attacks, including data confidentiality attacks, DoS attacks, power side-channel attacks, and photonic side-channel attacks. This makes it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, since the focus of the paper is on the security aspects of the memory, cs.ET and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories.
